<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="8" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[106,1112,151,417]" pageId="2" pageNumber="8">
Discussion: The species is characterized by a medially unpunctured zone of the clypeus. Punctures are restricted to the basolateral areas only. Body is all black except some red marks of the face. See 
<bibRefCitation author="Gadallah, N. S." box="[294,471,270,295]" journalOrPublisher="Efflatounia" pageId="2" pageNumber="8" pagination="31 - 40" part="4" refId="ref2565" refString="Gadallah, N. S. (2004): Scoliidae from the Western Region of Saudi Arabia (Hymenoptera: Aculeata). Efflatounia, 4: 31 - 40." title="Scoliidae from the Western Region of Saudi Arabia (Hymenoptera: Aculeata)" type="journal article" year="2004">Gadallah (2004)</bibRefCitation>
for description and key to the Arabian species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1775" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Scolia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1045,1112,270,294]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="8">Scolia</emphasis>
Fabricius, 1775
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Osten, T." box="[292,447,301,325]" journalOrPublisher="Entomofauna" pageId="2" pageNumber="8" pagination="9 - 16" part="26" refId="ref2658" refString="Osten, T. (2005 a). Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Scoliidenfauna des Oman (Hymenoptera, Scoliidae). Entomofauna, 26: 9 - 16." title="Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Scoliidenfauna des Oman (Hymenoptera, Scoliidae)" type="journal article" year="2005">Osten (2005a)</bibRefCitation>
discusses the possible conspecifity with 
<emphasis box="[903,1112,301,325]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" box="[903,970,301,325]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Scolia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Scolia</taxonomicName>
turkestanica
</emphasis>
Betrem, 1935. The reddish spots at the inner eye margin of the specimens from the UAE are barely visible due to the alcohol preservation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
